      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of August 21 Business Day article on planned Court TV series offering videotaped confessions of people accused of violent crimes such as murder</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Business Day last Monday about a planned Court TV series offering the videotaped confessions of people accused of violent crimes misstated the outcome of a case involving Daniel Rakowitz, who was taped confessing to the murder and dismemberment of a woman in Manhattan in 1989. He was tried and found not responsible by reason of insanity in 1991. He was not judged unfit to stand trial.</p>
      </block>
